choices.text: the elections held on 5 June 2011. Here, it is worth pointing out, in a way, in the midst of all the media coverage, that this has been the first general elections in which every eligible voter, in theory and exercise of citizens’ rights, could make the ultimate decision whether the political party he trusts and respects will have the appreciation and support and which will take the country forward or will be replaced by another political party that will make an attempt to do so.Therefore, there is no small factor that the dates of these elections will remain in the annals of Macedonian history, after 13 years of political anarchy, anarchy which primordially came as a result of the greedy and violent assimilation of the majority by the Albanian minority, through which the latter has clearly expressed its wish to remain apart from the majority and have its own political and state ideology, organization and system.This model was ventilated into the different political movements present in the Republic of Macedonia, and escalated to such a degree to which the ethnic majority has begun trying to adapt to meet the minority, and not the other way around.
